TITLE: Creating WebDriver Factory for Multiple Browsers in Java
DESCRIPTION: This Java class implements a WebDriverFactory that creates different WebDriver instances based on a system property, supporting multiple browsers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cucumber/docs/blob/main/content/docs/guides/browser-automation.md#2025-04-09_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.chrome.ChromeDriver;

public class WebDriverFactory {
    public static WebDriver createWebDriver() {
        String webdriver = System.getProperty("browser", "firefox");
        switch(webdriver) {
            case "firefox":
                return new FirefoxDriver();
            case "chrome":
                return new ChromeDriver();
            default:
                throw new RuntimeException("Unsupported webdriver: " + webdriver);
        }
    }
}
```

