TITLE: Using Cucumber Profiles in Rake Tasks
DESCRIPTION: Example of defining multiple Rake tasks that use different Cucumber profiles. This setup creates namespaced tasks for running features with different configurations defined in profiles.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cucumber/docs/blob/main/content/docs/tools/ruby.md#2025-04-09_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
require 'rubygems'
require 'cucumber'
require 'cucumber/rake/task'

namespace :features do
  Cucumber::Rake::Task.new(:non_js) do |t|
    t.profile = "webrat"
  end

  Cucumber::Rake::Task.new(:selenium) do |t|
    t.profile = "selenium"
  end
end
```

